1
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:49,270
-I mean...
-Hey...

2
00:00:50,230 --> 00:00:51,520
-I...
-Did I...

3
00:01:11,660 --> 00:01:12,800
What are you doing...

4
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:15,970
I'm sorry.

5
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,480
I'm sorry, Yeon-seo.

6
00:01:31,910 --> 00:01:32,950
Darn it!

7
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,490
Come here.

8
00:01:41,590 --> 00:01:43,880
-This way.
-It's raining!

9
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,300
-Go to the side!
-It's raining!

10
00:01:46,470 --> 00:01:48,229
Why are you doing this to me?

11
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,120
Thank you.

12
00:01:57,870 --> 00:01:59,229
I almost got caught.

13
00:02:01,110 --> 00:02:02,210
My wings!

14
00:02:10,220 --> 00:02:12,610
Goodness, my brother.

15
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:15,290
Please come to your senses.

16
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,750
That jerk.

17
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,390
That pervert. That fanatic.

18
00:02:47,190 --> 00:02:48,240
I'm sorry I'm late.

19
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:52,120
Where's Mr. Kim?

20
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,810
Let's go.

21
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:23,800
I'm fine.

22
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:25,680
Summer rain can give you a cold too.

23
00:03:26,090 --> 00:03:28,410
And you get a fever when you catch a cold.

24
00:03:28,770 --> 00:03:29,860
Do I?

25
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:32,240
You're wrong.

26
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:35,190
You get a fever when you catch a cold.

27
00:03:35,270 --> 00:03:36,240
Come here.

28
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,730
It's too suffocating! I don't like it.

29
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,270
Stay still.

30
00:03:47,550 --> 00:03:48,740
You can't do this.

31
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,470
From now on, you must never

32
00:03:51,550 --> 00:03:53,230
get sick or injured.

33
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:55,870
You shouldn't be alone either.

34
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:04,180
A Pilates instructor will come over
in the morning.

35
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,250
Check your condition.

36
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:08,280
Do cardio exercise and weight training
in the morning and stretch after that.

37
00:04:08,370 --> 00:04:09,720
You'll start getting back in shape.

38
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:11,450
Take a breath.

39
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:12,890
Why are you in a hurry?

40
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:14,790
You need to prepare yourself for war.

41
00:04:15,010 --> 00:04:15,970
From tomorrow...

42
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:18,480
No, from now on, it's war.

43
00:04:18,570 --> 00:04:19,620
I can take care of myself.

44
00:04:19,709 --> 00:04:21,000
Then why did you get drenched?

45
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:24,200
You're the one who dropped the bomb.

46
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:27,590
You announced your own comeback.

47
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:30,360
(A dancer speaks with his or her body.)

48
00:04:30,450 --> 00:04:31,770
I regained my sight,

49
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:34,590
and nothing is wrong
with my body and mind.

50
00:04:34,670 --> 00:04:35,990
I will speak to you more in detail

51
00:04:36,090 --> 00:04:38,850
with my dance on my return performance.

52
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:42,200
Are you sure
you're physically and mentally healthy?

53
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:46,200
Just look at me.

54
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,100
Imagine that it's just

55
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,090
(you and me in this world.)

56
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:55,450
Yes, I am.

57
00:04:56,050 --> 00:04:57,120
I'm completely fine.

58
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:09,120
People are more excited to hear about
others' failure more than their success.

59
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:12,040
Those who applauded your comeback

60
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:14,310
will be the first ones

61
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,210
to criticize you if you fail.

62
00:05:16,910 --> 00:05:18,980
You're on the edge of a cliff.

63
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:20,660
Whether it be a cliff or the fiery pits,

64
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:23,480
it's me who's there, not you.

65
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:25,800
I'm the one in charge
of your comeback performance.

66
00:05:26,290 --> 00:05:29,050
If you fail, it will humiliate me too.

67
00:05:29,450 --> 00:05:30,520
Two weeks.

68
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:32,940
I'll give you two weeks.

69
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:34,340
Get your body back in shape

70
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:35,880
and get my approval first.

71
00:05:36,190 --> 00:05:37,470
If you fail,

72
00:05:37,550 --> 00:05:39,880
Geum Ni-na will be
the prima ballerina of Fantasia.

73
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:41,470
One week.

74
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,340
That's all I need.

75
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:50,840
Ni-na. Where are you? Ni-na.

76
00:05:54,409 --> 00:05:55,409
Ni-na.

77
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,660
Why are you out here?

78
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,020
Ru-na.

79
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:06,720
Director Ji.

80
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,100
I have something to tell you.

81
00:06:09,190 --> 00:06:10,950
Next time. I have an appointment.

82
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,800
Are you meeting Yeon-seo?

83
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,770
That's none of your business.

84
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,360
Don't go.

85
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:24,620
Geum Ni-na.

86
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:26,610
You told me to be selfish.

87
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:29,300
I'm going to

88
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:31,590
like you.

89
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,300
No.

90
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:34,659
I already do.

91
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,050
I'll pretend that I didn't hear that.

92
00:06:43,730 --> 00:06:45,270
It was since that night.

93
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:48,220
That night when you touched my ankle.

94
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:54,950
It feels like a big rock fell on my heart.

95
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:58,240
Why today?

96
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,800
Your biggest rival announced

97
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:03,270
her comeback after a three-year gap.

98
00:07:03,350 --> 00:07:04,620
But instead,

99
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:07,490
you decided to listen
to your useless emotions

100
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:09,150
and confessed to me.

101
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:11,270
I'm disappointed in you.

102
00:07:11,660 --> 00:07:12,890
"Useless"?

103
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:14,740
Let's not waste any time.

104
00:07:14,930 --> 00:07:18,050
I'm not Prince Charming you think I am.

105
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:19,620
Then you can tell me.

106
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,390
That's what I'm most curious about.

107
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:25,210
What kind of person are you?

108
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:27,020
I'm an evil person.

109
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:30,410
I'm beyond what you can imagine or handle.

110
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:32,520
I'm very evil.

111
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:39,520
I shouldn't have told him. I was too rash.

112
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:41,840
Once Yeon-seo returns,

113
00:07:41,940 --> 00:07:43,880
I'll be nothing short of a shadow again.

114
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:48,490
I thought he would care less about me
once that happens.

115
00:07:48,580 --> 00:07:50,120
I agree with him.

116
00:07:52,310 --> 00:07:54,700
You already act like a shadow,
so who will take notice of you?

117
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:56,409
Why are you scaring me?

118
00:07:56,490 --> 00:07:58,620
Where's your pride? Are you not angry?

119
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:01,920
You were looked down on as a ballerina
and also as a woman.

120
00:08:03,230 --> 00:08:04,820
That makes me so upset.

121
00:08:06,170 --> 00:08:08,210
But you're just being childish and crying.

122
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:09,700
Stop being a baby.

123
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:11,950
No one's going to fix this for you.

124
00:08:26,020 --> 00:08:28,000
I said, go. Please go.

125
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:30,070
There's no emergency.
The rain has stopped.

126
00:08:30,590 --> 00:08:31,790
It's getting late, so go.

127
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,980
Don't get kicked out again.

128
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:43,230
I feel like I did something wrong.

129
00:08:43,530 --> 00:08:45,550
Is it possible for an angel
to feel guilty?

130
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:47,450
Can an angel commit a sin?

131
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,340
Answer me. Who are you?

132
00:09:02,540 --> 00:09:04,300
I'm Kim Dan.

133
00:09:04,390 --> 00:09:05,670
Don't tell me your human name.

134
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:06,860
Tell me your real name.

135
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:08,440
What are you?

136
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,130
I'm Dan, an angel.

137
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:14,510
That's right. Then you must know

138
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:18,340
what'll happen to an angel if he gives up
on his mission and commit a sin.

139
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:23,050
I didn't commit a sin.
It just feels like I did.

140
00:09:23,140 --> 00:09:24,230
It feels like it?

141
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,090
You don't want to go up there, do you?

142
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,300
Would you like to turn into dust
right here?

143
00:09:30,390 --> 00:09:31,590
Are you threatening me?

144
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:33,480
You're a thug!

145
00:09:39,770 --> 00:09:40,650
Come on!

146
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:52,170
I still have time left!

147
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:55,160
An angel should only be obedient.

148
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:57,490
If you have other intentions,
you'll only be doomed.

149
00:09:57,590 --> 00:10:00,180
Just like how you can differentiate
what's holy from what's worldly,

150
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:01,730
and a good man from an evil one,

151
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,180
remember who is before you.

152
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:08,140
You've led cats and dogs into paradise.

153
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,650
It's the same with that woman, got it?

154
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:31,290
(Kim Dan)

155
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,990
(Kim Dan)

156
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:40,330
Excuse me. I'd like a bottle of soju.

157
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:51,590
Thank you.

158
00:12:01,090 --> 00:12:02,100
What brings you here?

159
00:12:02,190 --> 00:12:03,520
What about you?

160
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,360
Why are you here at this hour?

161
00:12:06,990 --> 00:12:08,530
Someone told me

162
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:11,120
that it is the best remedy
when my heart is on fire.

163
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,290
Okay, then.

164
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:19,790
Your heart is on fire?

165
00:12:29,770 --> 00:12:31,450
Just quit if this is
how you'll do your job.

166
00:12:32,910 --> 00:12:34,700
-Pardon?
-I'll get you a new job.

167
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,280
I can get you a better paying job.

168
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:39,450
A job that can accommodate your needs.

169
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:42,090
What if I say I don't want to?

170
00:12:42,190 --> 00:12:43,770
"I don't want to"? Not, "I can't"?

171
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:45,700
-Why not?
-Even if I get fired,

172
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,470
I'll make Yeon-seo fire me.

173
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:50,370
This isn't your business to meddle with.

174
00:12:50,730 --> 00:12:52,220
You said you were going to help me.

175
00:12:53,590 --> 00:12:55,830
Have you forgotten what you need to do?
Or...

176
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,660
Or did you have a change of heart?

177
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:02,020
I keep my promises.

178
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:04,090
I'm going to fix you up

179
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:05,820
with Yeon-seo myself.

180
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:07,260
"Young Lady".

181
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:12,320
You keep calling her by her name.

182
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:13,820
That's been bothering me a lot.

183
00:13:14,390 --> 00:13:16,250
Seeing how you drop your honorifics
to your boss,

184
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,790
I doubt that you're good at your job.

185
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:21,250
Why are you getting angry at me?

186
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:25,120
I've already seen her alone

187
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,500
in the rain twice.

188
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:31,110
You were worried because Yeon-seo

189
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,050
was alone.

190
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,200
Is that why you got angry?

191
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:37,190
Listen.

192
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:39,910
I'm asking why you're not doing
your job...

193
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,340
What are you doing?

194
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:45,550
You're running a fever.

195
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:48,410
And your pupils are shaky too.

196
00:13:50,910 --> 00:13:51,920
And you're nervous.

197
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:55,450
I was right. You're definitely angry.

198
00:13:59,050 --> 00:14:01,070
I'm all for worrying about Young Lady.

199
00:14:01,170 --> 00:14:02,270
I'm all for it,

200
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:05,570
but I'll take care of my job myself.

201
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:16,250
What was that?

202
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:20,520
She's a puppy or a kitty.

203
00:14:22,410 --> 00:14:24,180
She's a pine tree or grass.

204
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:26,110
Yeon-seo is just a client.

205
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,270
After I make Yeon-seo fall in love,

206
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,550
I will go back up there no matter what.

207
00:14:51,770 --> 00:14:52,990
I wasn't angry.

208
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,620
No. Actually, I was.

209
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:00,950
I'm so livid.

210
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:04,750
(You were worried because Yeon-seo)

211
00:15:05,090 --> 00:15:06,420
(was alone.)

212
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,640
(Is that why you got angry?)

213
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,900
It's because of ballet.

214
00:15:11,730 --> 00:15:12,710
I barely

215
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:15,120
managed to get you this far.

216
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:17,200
I just need to put you on the stage.

217
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:20,620
Then, I can keep my promise to you.

218
00:15:22,070 --> 00:15:24,230
But how could you kiss a mere secretary?

219
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:40,770
Why are all the curtains closed?

220
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:43,510
It's so dark in here.

221
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:53,530
Young Lady.

222
00:15:56,130 --> 00:15:57,620
What are you doing here?

223
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,380
Did you stay up all night?

224
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,370
Absence without notice
and leaving a workplace

225
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:06,040
can be the reason for dismissal, right?

226
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,000
Dan?

227
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:08,460
Did something happen last night?

228
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:09,810
(I know what your wishes are.)

229
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:12,500
I will grant your wish.

230
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:17,430
Because I listened to you...

231
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:19,550
What did I do?

232
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,410
I see. You're talking about Dan?

233
00:16:24,070 --> 00:16:25,790
-He has a crush on you.
-No, he doesn't.

234
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:26,980
He doesn't.

235
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:29,230
Did you ask that to his face?

236
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,980
Of course, he'd deny that.

237
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:32,910
No, I didn't do that.

238
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,770
Please refrain from spreading and making

239
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,620
groundless rumors starting now.

240
00:16:42,950 --> 00:16:45,590
There's no way my instincts are wrong.

241
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:48,660
Besides, fire this jerk.

242
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:50,080
For good this time.

243
00:16:50,420 --> 00:16:51,660
Good morning.

244
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:57,240
Did you sleep well?

245
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:58,340
Ms. Jung.

246
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,550
Tell him that staying out overnight can be
a reason for his dismissal.

247
00:17:04,460 --> 00:17:05,700
Something urgent came up.

248
00:17:06,089 --> 00:17:07,500
Please tell her that I'm sorry.

249
00:17:09,650 --> 00:17:11,410
I'm sorry, Young Lady.

250
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:14,619
What's wrong with you?
Why are you so polite?

251
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,819
I had been overstepping my boundaries.

252
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:19,859
I will focus on my work from now on.

253
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,550
I'm glad to hear that.

254
00:17:24,390 --> 00:17:25,710
I'm going to practice.

255
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,910
I have something to tell you.

256
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:52,870
Go ahead.

257
00:17:55,850 --> 00:17:56,870
Last night...

258
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,460
I was...

259
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:13,020
I'm sorry about last night.

260
00:18:13,770 --> 00:18:14,870
Please forget what happened.

261
00:18:19,430 --> 00:18:20,500
What do you mean?

262
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:22,570
Nothing happened last night between us.

263
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,500
You and I...

264
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:27,750
Right. Nothing happened.

265
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:29,550
Nothing at all.

266
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:30,880
Something happened between us.

267
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:32,380
No, nothing happened.

268
00:18:32,470 --> 00:18:33,650
No, it did.

269
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:36,550
What's your point, you jerk?

270
00:18:36,810 --> 00:18:38,090
You told me to forget about it.

271
00:18:38,190 --> 00:18:40,470
I'm trying to pretend and move on.

272
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,480
You're so clueless.

273
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,530
Can't you play along?

274
00:18:42,620 --> 00:18:44,380
I can't lie that nothing happened
when it did.

275
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,150
-To pretend that...
-Stop.

276
00:18:47,810 --> 00:18:49,350
That's exactly my point.

277
00:18:49,450 --> 00:18:50,900
