550
00:37:24,860 --> 00:37:26,320
Hey, forget about your body.

551
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:28,820
Do you want to disappear into the universe
as dust?

552
00:37:29,270 --> 00:37:30,980
My mission isn't over yet.

553
00:37:31,460 --> 00:37:33,310
And about that mission...

554
00:37:37,150 --> 00:37:39,260
I have to help her find her love, right?

555
00:37:39,380 --> 00:37:40,450
But does that have to be

556
00:37:40,520 --> 00:37:44,270
love between a human and another human?

557
00:37:45,950 --> 00:37:46,950
It has to be, right?

558
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:54,030
I somehow ended up kissing her,

559
00:37:54,380 --> 00:37:56,020
my heart suddenly begins to beat

560
00:37:56,230 --> 00:37:58,090
(as if it's broken.)

561
00:37:59,270 --> 00:38:01,070
(Then I suddenly feel suffocated.)

562
00:38:01,290 --> 00:38:02,710
Rib asked me

563
00:38:03,460 --> 00:38:05,380
if I have feelings

564
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:07,460
for Yeon-seo.

565
00:38:07,540 --> 00:38:08,600
Gosh.

566
00:38:08,690 --> 00:38:10,400
What am I going to do with you?

567
00:38:15,950 --> 00:38:17,000
Let's see.

568
00:38:17,390 --> 00:38:19,070
It was about 15 years ago.

569
00:38:19,520 --> 00:38:22,500
There was this angel
who was in charge of art.

570
00:38:28,050 --> 00:38:30,070
(He took on the human form)

571
00:38:30,160 --> 00:38:32,350
(and was given a mission)

572
00:38:32,530 --> 00:38:34,030
(to inspire artists.)

573
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,950
No, not this one.

574
00:38:39,230 --> 00:38:40,670
I don't like it!

575
00:38:43,580 --> 00:38:46,220
What the hell went wrong this time?

576
00:38:46,620 --> 00:38:49,120
This is the 43rd time, for goodness' sake.

577
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:50,920
Where are you going?

578
00:38:51,020 --> 00:38:52,810
Give me another canvas!

579
00:38:53,620 --> 00:38:54,620
I failed!

580
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:58,150
(He met this person as he began
to grow tired of)

581
00:38:59,020 --> 00:39:00,520
(picky artists.)

582
00:40:02,520 --> 00:40:04,450
(I heard there's a chance
you can get confused,)

583
00:40:04,750 --> 00:40:06,290
(especially the angels of art.)

584
00:40:07,450 --> 00:40:09,240
(He got inspiration)

585
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:10,910
(confused with love.)

586
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:15,010
(An angel fell in love
with another being other than the deity?)

587
00:40:15,540 --> 00:40:16,590
(Is that possible?)

588
00:40:22,930 --> 00:40:27,070
So you can become a human with this?

589
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:29,140
No angel knows how, but...

590
00:40:30,890 --> 00:40:32,480
I have to make this confession.

591
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:51,740
From this moment on...

592
00:40:52,410 --> 00:40:53,410
No.

593
00:40:53,510 --> 00:40:55,580
From the very beginning,

594
00:40:56,410 --> 00:40:58,840
my love belonged to her.

595
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,070
I believe that You're the one

596
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:03,580
who helped us to meet

597
00:41:04,950 --> 00:41:06,220
and made us fall in love.

598
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:09,040
So please bless us.

599
00:41:11,860 --> 00:41:15,200
(Believing that you can love something
other than the deity)

600
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:17,800
(is an act of arrogance and sin.)

601
00:41:20,300 --> 00:41:22,500
What happened to that angel then?

602
00:41:28,570 --> 00:41:31,840
What do you think happened to an angel
who abandoned the deity?

603
00:41:38,520 --> 00:41:42,030
Dan, an angel, will be judged.

604
00:41:43,190 --> 00:41:44,230
You dared...

605
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:46,170
I want to live.

606
00:41:46,270 --> 00:41:49,160
(You dared to meddle in the life
that the deity had control over.)

607
00:41:51,330 --> 00:41:52,470
I like you so much

608
00:41:53,300 --> 00:41:54,410
that it's driving me insane.

609
00:41:54,490 --> 00:41:58,150
(You neglected and forgot
your mission, given to you by the deity.)

610
00:41:58,270 --> 00:42:00,210
(By not carrying it out, you have sinned.)

611
00:42:01,490 --> 00:42:02,500
Just look at me.

612
00:42:02,580 --> 00:42:05,790
Imagine that it's just you and me
in this world.

613
00:42:06,200 --> 00:42:07,380
(Above all,)

614
00:42:07,870 --> 00:42:09,400
(you've deluded yourself into thinking)

615
00:42:09,890 --> 00:42:12,790
(that you loved an insignificant being
more than the deity.)

616
00:42:14,290 --> 00:42:16,890
You will be dissipated.

617
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:05,590
-Dan.
-Ma'am, what is it?

618
00:43:06,210 --> 00:43:07,580
It's been hours.

619
00:43:07,670 --> 00:43:09,900
She's refusing to eat
and not letting anyone in.

620
00:44:09,180 --> 00:44:10,400
That's enough.

621
00:44:11,410 --> 00:44:12,550
Don't push yourself too hard.

622
00:44:22,380 --> 00:44:23,300
I said that's enough.

623
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:28,320
Did you forget?

624
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:30,380
I told you not to touch me.

625
00:44:34,520 --> 00:44:35,740
You're bleeding.

626
00:44:42,220 --> 00:44:43,310
So what?

627
00:44:47,720 --> 00:44:49,700
My toenails have fallen off many times.

628
00:44:49,780 --> 00:44:52,020
I've thrown away countless pairs
of bloody pointe shoes.

629
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:53,480
This is nothing.

630
00:45:00,600 --> 00:45:01,790
Finally,

631
00:45:02,670 --> 00:45:04,040
they look like a ballerina's feet.

632
00:45:13,230 --> 00:45:15,040
I didn't know you had to push yourself

633
00:45:16,620 --> 00:45:17,680
this much.

634
00:45:19,520 --> 00:45:20,890
You're going through so much pain.

635
00:45:24,980 --> 00:45:26,790
Let's call it a day, okay?

636
00:45:29,950 --> 00:45:31,270
Don't be ridiculous.

637
00:45:31,540 --> 00:45:32,950
I made a promise to Director Ji.

638
00:45:33,520 --> 00:45:36,120
I have to get back in shape within a week.

639
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,230
Listen to me. You can't continue
practicing with this foot.

640
00:45:42,450 --> 00:45:43,910
What if you get injured again?

641
00:45:44,420 --> 00:45:47,280
Are you going to return to being someone
who's in solitude and grumpy?

642
00:45:47,420 --> 00:45:49,980
None of this matters if you're unhappy.

643
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:56,350
I hate you.

644
00:45:57,840 --> 00:46:00,270
Don't be worried about me.
Don't care for me.

645
00:46:00,570 --> 00:46:01,540
I hate...

646
00:46:03,170 --> 00:46:04,620
receiving love.

647
00:46:05,720 --> 00:46:07,360
It makes me want to become weak.

648
00:46:09,240 --> 00:46:12,290
It makes me think it is okay to be weak.

649
00:46:15,970 --> 00:46:17,340
I thought you liked me.

650
00:46:19,680 --> 00:46:20,910
I really did.

651
00:46:22,450 --> 00:46:23,950
You said you existed because of me.

652
00:46:24,020 --> 00:46:26,750
You were the one who sweet-talked me.

653
00:46:27,730 --> 00:46:30,140
If you're neither a liar nor a spy,
then it's only one thing.

654
00:46:32,480 --> 00:46:33,760
Do you like me?

655
00:46:34,100 --> 00:46:37,490
(Believing that you can love something
other than the deity)

656
00:46:37,590 --> 00:46:39,780
(is an act of arrogance and sin.)

657
00:46:40,350 --> 00:46:41,770
You said you couldn't lie.

658
00:46:42,870 --> 00:46:44,130
Just say yes or no.

659
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:47,440
Did you like me?

660
00:46:50,910 --> 00:46:53,200
Do you?

661
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:05,080
No.

662
00:47:14,970 --> 00:47:16,160
All right, then.

663
00:47:20,300 --> 00:47:21,360
Get lost.

664
00:47:54,450 --> 00:47:56,380
(I had almost made a mistake,)

665
00:47:56,950 --> 00:47:59,060
(but I am currently focusing
on my mission.)

666
00:47:59,240 --> 00:48:00,660
(This is Dan, an angel.)

667
00:48:03,870 --> 00:48:06,590
(My subject has begun dancing once again.)

668
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:11,560
(She is very sensitive
and rough-tempered.)

669
00:49:09,810 --> 00:49:12,020
(I'm struggling alone without receiving)

670
00:49:12,410 --> 00:49:13,870
(any signs or prophecies.)

671
00:49:32,480 --> 00:49:34,230
(At first, her temper was the problem.)

672
00:49:35,160 --> 00:49:36,840
(But now, she's too busy)

673
00:49:37,980 --> 00:49:39,600
(to love anyone.)

674
00:49:41,490 --> 00:49:42,910
(Could there be a way)

675
00:49:44,010 --> 00:49:47,340
(for her to succeed
in both ballet and love?)

676
00:50:06,220 --> 00:50:07,630
(Mongyu Island, 2005)

677
00:50:07,710 --> 00:50:09,910
(The day I started ballet once again)

678
00:50:10,010 --> 00:50:12,040
(My first stage and my first audience)

679
00:50:18,550 --> 00:50:20,430
You're unbelievable!

680
00:50:21,890 --> 00:50:22,890
Young Lady!

681
00:50:24,960 --> 00:50:25,980
Wake up.

682
00:50:26,680 --> 00:50:27,880
It's morning!

683
00:50:30,730 --> 00:50:32,620
What date is today? What day is it?

684
00:50:32,720 --> 00:50:33,630
It's D-Day.

685
00:50:33,730 --> 00:50:36,090
It's been exactly a week
since your announcement.

686
00:50:38,730 --> 00:50:40,670
You shouldn't have stayed up all night
to practice.

687
00:50:40,770 --> 00:50:42,700
You really don't know
how to take care of yourself.

688
00:50:48,110 --> 00:50:50,700
Your aunt called so many times
this morning.

689
00:50:52,730 --> 00:50:53,740
Look at this.

690
00:50:54,010 --> 00:50:55,590
She calls me every five minutes.

691
00:51:00,390 --> 00:51:01,350
It's me.

692
00:51:03,600 --> 00:51:04,620
Now?

693
00:51:13,370 --> 00:51:14,900
You didn't come with him today.

694
00:51:15,790 --> 00:51:17,200
Please wait outside for me.

695
00:51:22,820 --> 00:51:25,520
You never answer my questions.

696
00:51:25,910 --> 00:51:27,480
How do you feel? Are you all right?

697
00:51:27,570 --> 00:51:30,520
Give me the withdrawal agreement on
the power of attorney. I brought my seal.

698
00:51:30,610 --> 00:51:32,590
My gosh, that's not ready yet.

699
00:51:32,690 --> 00:51:35,370
You said I had to sign it today.
That's why you told me to come out.

700
00:51:35,450 --> 00:51:36,650
Is that what you told her?

701
00:51:37,480 --> 00:51:40,470
My attorney is very meticulous.

702
00:51:40,550 --> 00:51:43,020
So my attorney needs to
check it a few more times.

703
00:51:43,330 --> 00:51:44,300
I'm sorry.

704
00:51:44,380 --> 00:51:46,190
-I'll get going then.
-Wait.

705
00:51:46,370 --> 00:51:49,270
Have some tea before you go.
I'm your aunt.

706
00:51:49,350 --> 00:51:51,550
We're not that close, you know.

707
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:54,590
You must've been very disappointed in me.

708
00:51:55,830 --> 00:51:57,270
To make up for that...

709
00:52:06,250 --> 00:52:09,340
-What's this?
-It's Fantasia's Night next week.

710
00:52:09,550 --> 00:52:10,880
Wear them to the event.

711
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:13,610
You know that I never serve my guests
at events.

712
00:52:13,690 --> 00:52:16,410
A very important Japanese investor
will be coming.

713
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:18,610
When I told him your name,
he said he'd come.

714
00:52:19,020 --> 00:52:21,790
We can't hold the show
for your return without his money.

715
00:52:21,880 --> 00:52:24,070
Sometimes,
you must do things you don't want to do.

716
00:52:24,160 --> 00:52:25,570
That's the world of adults.

717
00:52:25,660 --> 00:52:28,200
We decided to announce

718
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:32,600
that Fantasia will belong to you,
Yeon-seo.

719
00:52:38,060 --> 00:52:40,480
See how nice it is to start dancing again.

720
00:52:41,100 --> 00:52:44,350
You can walk with me like this
even without Dan.

721
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:47,300
He has no place to go.

722
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:48,760
Where did he go on his vacation?

723
00:52:50,950 --> 00:52:52,050
Well...

724
00:52:53,060 --> 00:52:54,090
What did he say?

725
00:52:54,220 --> 00:52:56,230
No. Don't tell me.

726
00:52:57,020 --> 00:52:59,010
Bosses who ask about
vacation spots are the worst.

727
00:53:01,390 --> 00:53:03,270
On the day of Fantasia's Night,

728
00:53:03,670 --> 00:53:06,490
I'll make him escort you no matter what.

729
00:53:08,600 --> 00:53:10,570
Let's hurry. I need to practice.

730
00:53:26,290 --> 00:53:28,930
I couldn't make him wait
at an empty house.

731
00:53:37,950 --> 00:53:41,020
This has been the longest week this year.

732
00:53:41,810 --> 00:53:42,840
Are you ready?

733
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:46,130
No, not at all. I'm totally doomed.

734
00:53:46,880 --> 00:53:48,110
It's a mess.

735
00:53:49,660 --> 00:53:50,620
Yeon-seo.

736
00:53:52,770 --> 00:53:53,780
What?

737
00:53:55,330 --> 00:53:57,130
Make yourself comfortable.
This will take long.

738
00:53:59,770 --> 00:54:02,020
-Where are we going?
-Well...

739
00:54:02,540 --> 00:54:03,600
To the beginning.

740
00:55:45,450 --> 00:55:46,470
This place...

741
00:55:46,550 --> 00:55:47,560
Do you remember?

742
00:55:48,450 --> 00:55:49,850
This feels familiar.

743
00:55:52,370 --> 00:55:53,280
What is this?

744
00:55:53,380 --> 00:55:54,380
What are you plotting?

745
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:56,020
Why did we come all the way here?

746
00:55:56,100 --> 00:55:57,200
Year 2005.

747
00:55:57,340 --> 00:55:59,190
Right before you went to Russia
for your studies.

748
00:55:59,660 --> 00:56:02,400
You went to an island
for a program called Visiting Ballet.

749
00:56:02,830 --> 00:56:03,980
How do you know that?

750
00:56:04,200 --> 00:56:05,510
Did you look into my past?

751
00:56:08,600 --> 00:56:09,790
Dan told you, right?

752
00:56:10,620 --> 00:56:11,890
She never misses a thing.

753
00:56:12,470 --> 00:56:13,390
I bet...

754
00:56:14,140 --> 00:56:15,510
Dan did everything here, right?

755
00:56:15,950 --> 00:56:17,000
Hey, Dan.

756
00:56:17,700 --> 00:56:18,860
Where are you? Come on out.

757
00:56:18,930 --> 00:56:21,140
Darn it. What's wrong with her?

758
00:56:22,640 --> 00:56:26,340
You think I wouldn't know where my prima
ballerina was born and how she grew up?

759
00:56:29,110 --> 00:56:33,810
I heard that you hid and cried
because you didn't want to do ballet.

760
00:56:35,400 --> 00:56:37,060
I didn't know that. How did he know that?

761
00:56:40,330 --> 00:56:41,550
I knew a kid.

762
00:56:42,220 --> 00:56:43,940
I've totally forgotten about the kid.

763
00:56:44,450 --> 00:56:45,550
That kid was

764
00:56:46,130 --> 00:56:47,370
my first audience.

765
00:56:49,030 --> 00:56:50,480
I danced for him.

766
00:56:51,410 --> 00:56:52,300
Just for him.

767
00:56:53,090 --> 00:56:54,090
Today,

768
00:56:54,490 --> 00:56:55,850
I'll watch you dance.

769
00:56:56,340 --> 00:56:58,410
The dance you did for your first audience.

770
00:56:58,760 --> 00:57:01,450
I don't remember.
I didn't have a routine since I was a kid.

771
00:57:07,700 --> 00:57:08,930
I can't make the turns.

772
00:57:12,480 --> 00:57:13,980
I can pull off other techniques

773
00:57:14,430 --> 00:57:16,540
once I get my muscles in shape
and practice more.

774
00:57:19,140 --> 00:57:20,450
But I can't make the turns.

775
00:57:22,820 --> 00:57:23,890
That's expected.

776
00:57:25,520 --> 00:57:27,660
You didn't dance for three years.
It's only been a week.

777
00:57:27,840 --> 00:57:29,640
Did you think I'd expect you
to be perfect?

778
00:57:30,340 --> 00:57:32,380
You're too confident of yourself.

779
00:57:35,490 --> 00:57:38,190
I wanted to see how determined you were.

780
00:57:40,300 --> 00:57:41,300
Your rhomboid,

781
00:57:41,700 --> 00:57:43,590
spinal erectors, and the soleus muscles.

782
00:57:44,160 --> 00:57:46,330
It took you a week to get them this far.

783
00:57:46,900 --> 00:57:47,870
It's a miracle.

784
00:57:52,120 --> 00:57:53,980
Well said, Rib.

785
00:57:54,060 --> 00:57:55,080
Take it easy.

786
00:57:55,560 --> 00:57:57,900
Don't worry about turnout, balance,
or anything else.

787
00:57:58,240 --> 00:57:59,380
Dance like your first time.

788
01:01:13,990 --> 01:01:14,960
(Good news.)

789
01:01:15,940 --> 01:01:17,700
(It looks like Yeon-seo,
who was icy cold,)

790
01:01:18,570 --> 01:01:20,820
(who was like an empty and noisy gong,)

791
01:01:21,610 --> 01:01:25,270
(is about to begin something.)

792
01:01:26,590 --> 01:01:28,430
(Her beginnings seems very humble,)

793
01:01:29,050 --> 01:01:32,000
(but her future will hold love.)

794
01:01:33,760 --> 01:01:35,550
(I am about to finish my mission.)

795
01:01:36,880 --> 01:01:37,760
(But...)

796
01:01:39,160 --> 01:01:42,550
(why is my heart in so much pain?)

797
01:02:01,820 --> 01:02:03,020
Why are you crying?

798
01:02:05,080 --> 01:02:06,320
Were you disappointed?

799
01:02:10,620 --> 01:02:11,860
That was so pretty.

800
01:02:13,090 --> 01:02:15,860
That was the prettiest thing
I've ever seen.

801
01:02:53,780 --> 01:02:57,220
(Angel's Last Mission: Love)

802
01:02:58,410 --> 01:02:59,990
(You're smiling brightly, aren't you?)

803
01:03:02,020 --> 01:03:02,980
You look pretty.

804
01:03:03,080 --> 01:03:04,620
Don't you think this is too much?

805
01:03:04,700 --> 01:03:06,290
("She was very beautiful.")

806
01:03:06,380 --> 01:03:08,790
"She was the prettiest."

807
01:03:08,880 --> 01:03:09,970
It's true!

808
01:03:10,060 --> 01:03:11,070
(I'll fight with you.)

809
01:03:11,160 --> 01:03:14,550
(I want to see you become
the center of Fantasia.)

810
01:03:14,960 --> 01:03:17,020
(About how the chandelier fell...)

811
01:03:17,200 --> 01:03:18,550
(I'm feeling nervous.)

812
01:03:18,910 --> 01:03:22,160
(You save me and help me out.)

813
01:03:22,250 --> 01:03:24,200
But why don't you like me?

814
01:03:24,410 --> 01:03:27,230
(How can I not like you?)
